The compiler contains an Integrated Development Environment(IDE) with Debugger and built-in Dynamic-Help-System and a compendium of example sourcecode.
(Include-files for using the WinAPI are included.)

---
(PS: Advantage of ConsoleCompiler: it's easier for beginners than the PBWin-Compiler, because you don't have to care for windows-stuff in your programs if you prefer so. But you can create win-API-apps with the above include-files if you want.

Second Advantage: this compiler contains a fully-fledged Graphic-Library with all sorts of graphic commands, so you can utilize full graphical windows in your programs, just with easy PBasic-commands without ever needing to use the windows-API!

Third Advantage: you can easily use all your old QuickBasic sources from DOS times , since PBCC is 95% compatible to QBasic/Quickbasic/GWBasic/BasicA/TurboBasic etc.)
